<HEADLINE>
PREMIER ORDERS GOVERNMENT TO OPERATE DURING NEW YEAR HOLIDAY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb. 15 (CNA) 02/15/07  21:59:31 (By Y.L. Kao)
</P>
<P>
Premier Su Tseng-chang said Wednesday that government agencies
will continue to work during the Chinese New Year holiday and he
ordered agency heads to determine and designate in advance the
skeleton operations that will continue during the upcoming
holiday period.
</P>
<P>
Su made the remarks during a Cabinet meeting prior to the Feb. 18
Lunar Chinese New Year festival, while giving away red envelopes
containing auspicious sayings to Cabinet staff members and
wishing them a happy New Year.
</P>
<P>
He noted that he floated the concept of "holiday services" at the
first meeting of the Cabinet following its reorganization last
year, adding that as the government cannot simply cease
functioning, all level of agencies must come up with contingency
plans and designate personnel to deal with unexpected situations
during the holiday.
</P>
<P>
Banks were told to ensure that their ATMs were restocked during
the nine-day holiday, and Su also instructed police authorities
to coordinate with contractors to decrease construction barriers
and enclosures located on main traffic routes around the country,
adding that traffic control should be continued during the
holiday.
</P>
<P>
As for the problems of criminals selling meat from deceased and
sick hogs, Su said that his administration will adopt stricter
penalties for offenders and step up a crackdown on those who
those who ignore health regulations and continue selling
questionable meat.
</P>
